Here Jesus appeared before the disciples and after the resurrection.
But most of all, the sanctuary in Jerusalem.
Believers here pass through the Way of Sorrow or the Cross of Jesus (in Latin - Via Dolorosa).
It begins at the fortress of Antony - Pretoria - where there was a court, and on the streets of the Old City leads to the Temple of the Tomb of the Lord on Mount Golgotha - to the place of the Crucifixion, the Stone of the anointing and the place of the burial of Jesus.
Here is the symbolic Christian Pup of the Earth, symbolizing the salvation of humanity.
And the monastery of the Holy Cross in Jerusalem will be built in the place where, according to Christian legend, the tree grew, from which the cross was made for the crucifixion of Jesus.
In Jerusalem there is also the holiest place for Jews - the Wall of Tears, left over from the temple destroyed by the Romans in 70 AD.
According to tradition, people of different confessions leave here notes with wishes, which are then fulfilled.
Make a journey through the vertical
The ruins of the fortress of Massad remained from a secret refuge from enemies, which Herod the Great built in 25 BC for his family.
They are located on steep cliffs in the mountains at an altitude of 450 m above sea level.
And only those who are interested in mountaineering can reach them with their own pace.
The rest on this historical peak is delivered by a lift on a cable car.
