From Friday evening to sundown on Saturday, markets, shops, public transport stop working.
On Sunday mornings, the working week begins.
In many cafes, restaurants and hotels - only kosher food, excluding pork, seafood, shellfish and dishes in which milk and meat are combined.
There are a large selection of dishes made from lamb and beef, soups and desserts made with coconut milk, traditional Jewish hummus paste, a variety of sauces, balls of ground nut - phallel, fruits and vegetables.
