However, from a conversation with the head of the interactive 3D technology group at the Cambridge laboratory of Microsoft, Sharam Izadi, it follows that for the scientists of this company glasses is the stage passed.
They are seduced by the prospect of manipulating virtual objects in the air with their bare hands, creating virtual open spaces.
- Please tell me, in general terms, what is your research team doing?
- We are engaged in human-machine interaction, but at the same time we are trying to push the boundaries of this interaction.
While humanity in the mass is stuck at the stage of working with pixels on the flat screen, sometimes typos in them with a finger.
