It is not used to determine the depth of the object.
Potentially more cameras could solve the problem...
Or make it worse by increasing the required amount of calculations.
It would be nice to create a flexible analogue of Kinect, play with the curvature of the cameras and see how it will help in three-dimensional definition of the position.
As far as I remember, Microsoft, unlike Google, did not present its glasses to the public.
